{"key":"processedPost-10037999","value":{"id":10037999,"first":10030215,"last":10050684,"when":1237999554,"utime":"03/25/09 07:45 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>azshroomer said:</strong><br />Im asking because I need lots of spawn. (Roughly 16 Quarts or more)<br />I can refrigerate extra.</blockquote><br />For small amounts like that, I'd suggest sticking with quart jars.&nbsp; You want to prove your spawn before putting into a large bag anyway.&nbsp; I use the large gusseted spawn bags, and each one holds six quarts of rye berries, when filled 1/3 full.&nbsp; This is about right because you want a plenum of air space above your grains at least as large as the volume of grains.<br />I always inoculate quart jars as my 'grain masters' and once I know they're contaminant free, I use each of them to inoculate 2 of the spawn bags, filled with six quarts of rye.&nbsp; This ensures I don't lose a large amount if the culture is contaminated.<br />Don't waste money on an impulse sealer.&nbsp; Get bailing tie wire from your local hardware store and use this to tie the bags shut at the top like a loaf of bread.&nbsp; This enables you to open the bag later without cutting it.&nbsp; I get two uses from each spawn bag, thus cutting the price in half.<br />RR"}}